    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-08-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-08-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="471"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Barrett</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-08-04">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 4, 1897</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 130.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 212, of the 22d of June last, reporting the arrangements made by
                    you in conjunction with the Siamese Government for the payment of the honorarium
                        <pb facs="0512" n="478" xml:id="pg_478"/> and expenses of the arbitrator,
                    Sir Nicholas Hannen, in the Cheek case, and to say that your action in the
                    matter is approved by the Department.</p>
                <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
